 main accretion center in the W51e2 complex is\nW51e2-E rather than W51e2-W. Finally, W51e2-NW and W51e8, although less dense,\nare also hot cores and contain a significant amount of molecular gas (~30 and\n70 solar masses, respectively). We speculate that they may host high-mass YSOs\neither at a previous evolutionary stage or with lower mass than W51e2-E and\nW51e2-W.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Jan 2016 18:17:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-04-27"}
